cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the application of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in image classification tasks, specifically using privileged information (segmentation masks) to improve the performance of the learning algorithm. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses the incorporation of domain knowledge and common sense concepts, which could potentially fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) categories. Finally, the experiments involve benchmark datasets commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
